title: Top Democrats Question Their Party’s Strategy as Midterm Worries Grow
description: Leading lawmakers and strategists are openly doubting the party’s kitchen-sink approach, saying Democrats have failed to unite around one central message.
dc:creator: Lisa Lerer, Katie Glueck and Reid J. Epstein
media:description: Abortion rights demonstrators prepared for an event last month in Madison, Wis., hosted by Gov. Tony Evers, a Democrat who is in a tight race for re-election.
